# .cursorrules — Algorand Explorer

project_type: "Frontend-only API dashboard"
stack: ["Vite", "React", "TypeScript", "Tailwind CSS", "shadcn/ui", "Lucide React", "Recharts"]
theme: {
  background: "#0E0E0E",
  text: "#E6E6E6",
  accent: "#F1CB83",
  font: "Chakra Petch"
}
folder_conventions:
  - /pages: all page entry components (e.g., MainPage.tsx, DebugPage.tsx)
  - /components: all UI blocks (e.g., AddressInput, ASATokenList)
  - /lib/api: API wrappers (e.g., fetchASAStats.ts, fetchNFD.ts)
  - /types: shared interfaces from ASAStats and NFD schemas
  - All file names camelCase, components PascalCase
  - Avoid deep nesting (max depth 2 inside /components or /lib)

state_management: "React local state only (useState/useEffect), no Zustand"
backend: "None — fetch from ASA Stats and NFD APIs only"
auth: "API token hardcoded/test only for now — no auth flow"

currency_toggle:
  - Header must include currency toggle (ALGO/USD) with shadcn/ui Switch component
  - Toggle state managed in App.tsx and passed down to components
  - When ALGO mode: all values displayed in ALGO (remove "ALGO Value USD" field)
  - When USD mode: all values displayed in USD
  - ProfileSummary program breakdown values change based on currency toggle
  - AssetAccordionCard and other components respect currency toggle
  - Use Lucide icons: DollarSign for USD, Coins for ALGO
  - Toggle should be compact and right-aligned in header

ui_library:
  - Use shadcn/ui components for all UI elements
  - Use Lucide React icons exclusively (no other icon libraries)
  - Import icons from 'lucide-react' package
  - Prefer shadcn/ui Button, Card, Input, Badge, Alert, Switch components
  - Use shadcn/ui charts (Recharts-based) for data visualization
  - Available chart components: LineChart, BarChart, PieChart, AreaChart, RadarChart

emoji_guidelines:
  - Use minimal emoji, prefer color circles: 🟡🔴
  - Use 🟢 for success/positive states
  - Use 🟡 for warning/attention states  
  - Use 🔴 for error/negative states
  - Avoid text emojis, use Lucide icons instead

style_rules:
  - Use Tailwind classes directly (no CSS modules or styled-components)
  - All components must support dark mode by default
  - Font must be Chakra Petch (imported via Google Fonts in index.css)
  - Prefer bordered containers over card shadows
  - Use `text-sm`, `text-lg`, `tracking-tight`, `rounded-md`, `hover:opacity-90` patterns
  - Use shadcn/ui theming system for consistent styling

api_usage:
  - Use `fetchASAStats(address: string): Promise<EvaluatedAccount>` from /lib/api
  - Use `fetchNFD(address: string): Promise<NFDMetadata | null>`
  - Do not wrap fetches in Zustand or Context
  - Validate address input before sending to API

testing & debug:
  - DebugPage must log full ASA Stats response to console
  - Display JSON preview in a `<pre>` or scrollable viewer
  - Include visible error states if address is invalid or API fails

component_principles:
  - Each component should accept typed props and be reusable
  - All external API types go in `/types`, no inline `any`
  - Avoid prop drilling deeper than 2 levels
  - Optional fields (e.g., `avatar`, `unit`, `image`) must be null-safe
  - Use shadcn/ui components as building blocks
  - Import Lucide icons with descriptive names

ui_behavior:
  - MainPage: input field > fetch > display profile summary
  - ProfileSummary → TokenList + NFTList + NFDTag (modular)
  - Do not rely on global state or router-based memory
  - Minimal interactions, no animations unless added later
  - Use shadcn/ui components for consistent UX
  - Currency toggle affects all value displays throughout the app

build_goals:
  - Zero-config deploy (e.g., Netlify-ready)
  - No runtime errors in absence of NFD/ASA data
  - Works with both `.algo` names and raw Algorand addresses
  - shadcn/ui components properly configured
  - Lucide icons optimized and tree-shaken
  - Charts integrated for portfolio visualization